# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## Disclose in chat

When this rule materially guides your response or edits, state in the Cursor chat that you applied it — mention `.cursor/rules/conventions.mdc` (one short line is enough).

## How to verify

- Run `yarn test:typecheck` and ESLint on touched files (`yarn test:all` or project lint command as in `docs/memory/techContext.md`).
- Confirm new components use named exports, functional components with hooks, and no new `@ts-ignore` or unnecessary `any`.